This paper discusses efficient algorithms for learning a linear predictor from examples when the learner can only view a few attributes of each training example. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper focuses on learning from limited data, we believe that cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.SI.
